orker` depends on `core`\n\nCurrently, the root file has `api` before `core`, which violates the build order requirement for composite projects.\n\n**File: `/workspace/tsconfig.json`**\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },      // ← WRONG: Listed before core\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" }      // ← WRONG: Listed after its dependents\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Correct order should be:**\n```json\n{\n  \"files\": [],\n  \"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" },      // core has no dependencies\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },       // api depends on core\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" }     // worker depends on core\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## BREAKAGE #4: DEPENDENCY VERSION CONFLICT\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/packages/core/package.json`\n\n**Issue:** The `zod` version is pinned to `3.19.0`, which is too old for the API being used in the code. The code uses `z.pipe()` which requires zod >= 3.22.\n\n**File: `/workspace/packages/core/package.json` (Lines 10-13)**\n```json\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"zod\": \"3.19.0\",                  // ← BREAKAGE: Too old, doesn't support z.pipe()\n    \"better-sqlite3\": \"^11.0.0\"\n  },\n```\n\n**File: `/workspace/packages/core/src/validation.ts` (Lines 20-22, 28-30, 33-36)**\n```typescript\nexport const userIdSchema = z\n  .string()\n  .pipe(z.coerce.number().int().positive('User ID must be a positive integer'));\n  // ↑ z.pipe() requires zod >= 3.22\n\n// ...\n\nexport const userFiltersSchema = z.object({\n  role: roleSchema.optional(),\n  search: z.string().optional(),\n  limit: z\n    .string()\n    .pipe(z.coerce.number().int().min(1).max(100))  // ← z.pipe() usage\n    .optional()\n    .default('20'),\n  offset: z\n    .string()\n    .pipe(z.coerce.number().int().min(0))           // ← z.pipe() usage\n```\n\n**Note:** zod 3.19.0 was released in September 2023, but `z.pipe()` was added in version 3.22. The current c